==English==

===Etymology===
The concept has been borrowed from mathematics and technology terminology, from ''[[step function]]''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[step]] [[change]]}}

# A [[sudden]] change in the [[value]] of some [[variable]], especially a [[discontinuous]] one
#* ''The report, stark and uncompromising, marks a '''step change''' in Europe's own role in pushing for international action to combat climate change, as it will be used in a bid to commit the EU to ambitious new targets for cutting emissions of greenhouse gases.'' - The Independent, 10/01/07

====Usage notes====
Originally used in the power supply industry, this now seems to be used instead of [[quantum leap]].

